From: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2020 14:52:07 -0400
Subject: drm/amdkfd: fix ref count leak when pm_runtime_get_sync fails
Git-commit: 1c1ada37af6ee6fb9cfc8da6a56cc83208cd8d6f
Patch-mainline: v5.9-rc1
References: jsc#SLE-12680, jsc#SLE-12880, jsc#SLE-12882, jsc#SLE-12883, jsc#SLE-13496, jsc#SLE-15322

The call to pm_runtime_get_sync increments the counter even in case of
failure, leading to incorrect ref count.
In case of failure, decrement the ref count before returning.

Reviewed-by: Rajneesh Bhardwaj <rajneesh.bhardwaj@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Patrik Jakobsson <pjakobsson@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_process.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_process.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_process.c
index 5a0391db8b29..a1e69b29b162 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_process.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_process.c
@@ -1117,8 +1117,10 @@ struct kfd_process_device *kfd_bind_process_to_device(struct kfd_dev *dev,
 	 */
 	if (!pdd->runtime_inuse) {
 		err = pm_runtime_get_sync(dev->ddev->dev);
-		if (err < 0)
+		if (err < 0) {
+			pm_runtime_put_autosuspend(dev->ddev->dev);
 			return ERR_PTR(err);
+		}
 	}
 
 	err = kfd_iommu_bind_process_to_device(pdd);
